<! [CDATA[
 National Bank of Canada Logo
The National Bank of Canada is the sixth largest commercial bank in Canada. It is headquartered in Montreal, and has branches in most Canadian provinces and 2.4 million personal clients. National Bank is the largest bank in Quebec, and the second largest financial institution in the province, after Desjardins credit union. National Bank’s Institution Number is 006 and its SWIFT code is BNDCCAMMINT. As of October 31, 2019, National Bank had a network of 422 branches and 939 automated teller machines in Canada.
You can download theNBClogo on full-version of the page.
